They think that there are two possible alternatives when it comes to abortion, such as the spread of an unsafe health centre or the child being born in poverty and bringing harm to the country, Ilgar Ibrahimoglu told Trend newspaper.

The situation is very serious. In 2011, 11% of all pregnancies ended in abortions, while 78% of these abortions were not supported by the state and included underage girls who became pregnant after experiencing rape.

"Government control over all types of births is absolutely required because all the economic and social problems stem from the fact that the government has just been concentrating on being a tool of one family and solved a few other problems. So, when a family is taken care of by a feudal family, our entire economy and society is just a tool for their economy and society". According to epidemiologists, the statistics are more or less of the same level. "One way or another, our prenatal examinations are absolutely sufficient, since our turnover is rather high and, as a result, complications are frequent", the head of the department noted.
